## Architecture Verification

✅ **Layer Hierarchy** (Golden Rule: No Skipping)
```
Controller → Service → Repository → Database
```
- Controller asks only Service
- Service asks only Repository
- Repository asks only Database

✅ **Separation of Concerns**
- Entity: Data only
- DTO: API contract only
- Repository: Database only
- Service: Business logic only
- Controller: HTTP translation only

✅ **OOP Principles**
- **Encapsulation**: Private fields, controlled access via getters/setters
- **Abstraction**: DTOs hide entity structure; Service interface hides implementation
- **Polymorphism**: Service interface allows Spring to inject implementation
- **Inheritance**: Repository inherits from JpaRepository
- **Single Responsibility**: Each class has one reason to change

---

## How to Test Locally

### Prerequisites
```bash
# 1. Start PostgreSQL server
# 2. Create database
psql -U postgres -c "CREATE DATABASE employeedb;"

# 3. Build the project
cd StaffForge
./gradlew build

# 4. Run tests
./gradlew test

# 5. Start the application
./gradlew bootRun
```

### Manual Testing
```bash
# Get all employees
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees

# Create employee
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "position": "Software Engineer"
  }'

# Get employee by ID
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1

# Update employee
curl -X PUT http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1 \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "firstName": "Jane",
    "lastName": "Smith",
    "email": "jane@example.com",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "position": "Marketing Manager"
  }'

# Delete employee
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1
```

