## Architecture Verification

✅ **Frontend Layer Hierarchy** (Golden Rule: No Skipping)
```
Component (UI Rendering)
    ↓ asks
Hook / State Management
    ↓ asks
Service (API Calls)
    ↓ asks
Backend API
```

✅ **Separation of Concerns**
- **Types**: Contract definition only
- **Service**: HTTP communication only
- **Hook**: State management only
- **Components**: UI rendering only
- **App**: Orchestration only

✅ **OOP Principles in Frontend**
- **Encapsulation**: Form state, hook state hidden from components
- **Abstraction**: Service abstracts HTTP; Hook abstracts state; Components abstract rendering
- **Polymorphism**: Custom hooks provide flexible state management
- **Inheritance**: Reusable component patterns
- **Single Responsibility**: Each file has one reason to change

